Growing in a cut-over pine savanna in dry sandy loam (Troup association, hilly; thermic Grossarenic Paleudults). With Amorpha herbacea, Astragalus sp., Carya pallida, Cnidoscolus stimulosus, Crataegus flava, Diospyros virginiana, Evolvulus sp., Ilex vomitoria, Lechea sp., Lespedeza sp., Nyssa sylvatica, Opuntia humifusa, Panicum sp., Pinus palustris, P. taeda, Prunus serotina, Pteridium aquilinum, Quercus incana, Q. laevis, Q. margaretta, Q. nigra, Q. velutina, Rhus copallina, Rubus sp., Sassafras albidum, Vaccineum arboreum and Vitis rotundifolia. To the N side of a pineline right-of-way, about 0.25 mi SW of county roads 127/106, 0.45 mi SW of US Rt. 82, and around 3 mi WSW of Billingsley. Elev. 460 ft. T19N, R13E, Sec4, SW 1/4 of SE 1/4. 32°38'48"N, 86°46'18"W. UTM 16 521425E, 3611941N.
